@node feat "List of currect Features"

  * 2-4 players (actually max. could be around 16...)
  * Limited vision ranges
  * Units for air, ground, sea & underwater action
  * Limited fuel (excluding ground units)
  * Ranged Attacks: Artillery, Anti-Air, Torpedos, damaging terrain
  * Tech-Level Development (currently automatic)
  * Transporters and carriers
  * Submarine unit: dive & surface modes
  * Combat Report
  * Repair & refuel in cities & tranporter/carrier units
  * TerrainDamage Threat System; risky terrains
  * Message System
  * Multitasking (..but some busy-loops..)
  * Mouse-keyboard interface; optional Panel Buttons
  * Map Editor
  * Editors for Unit & Hex Types
  * LORES-LACED HIRES / DBL @{"(?)" link bugs} / OVERSCAN Screenmode Support
  * 3 ZoomLevels; showing Units & Production
  * Spacial Abilities: building roads & bridges
  * City size effects on production times
  * Infantry features: hiding, antitank. engineers etc.
@endnode



@node requ "Requirements"

  This version requires about 2 MB memory, .5 chip should be enough.
  There is no OS-requirements (as far as I know..) but 4x Zoom is not
  available under Exec V 36.

  OCS should be enough although ECS & AGA screenmodes are supported.

  Harddrive is recommended, but it is possible to play from disks.
@endnode



@node inst "Harddisk Installation"

  1. Extract archive.  It'll create a subdirectory (*).
     But You have already done this since You are reading =)
  2. Add following lines to S:Startup-Sequence or S:User-Startup

     Assign PowerBattle: {path, the directory (*) from step 1 }
     Assign PBMaps: PowerBattle:Maps
     Assign PBSave: PowerBattle:Save

  3. Move @{"s/powerbattle.config" link pref}  to  S:
  4. Reboot (or execute assigns)


  (*) path ends either /PowerBattle or :PowerBattle
@endnode



@node bugs "Troubleshooting & Bugs"

  Known Bugs:

  - Zoom X 4 doesn't work on all Amigas.  Will Guru if not.
    Try, and don't use if it doesn't work.
  - Game may jam with unsuitable starting values on new game.

  I'd guess PowerBattle doesn't like exotic screenmodes.  So please
  try disabling ModePromotion &  setting WB to normal PAL if you
  encounter messy graphics or other uncommon 'features'.

  In configuration file, real screenmode-ID's can be tested.  Some
  will work while others probably won't.  It looks like 640 x 400 is
  the largest screensize that will work properly.

  If you panic, try pressing SHIFT-Q (or plain q if in Map Editor).
  It will take you to the main menu, where you can select Quit to
  leave the program.

  If you want to report a bug, tell me your hardware & OS
  configuration.  You can also send me a saved game where a spesific
  bug occurs.

  @{" Reports bugs to me!!  " link auth}
@endnode



@node pref "Preferences & Configuration File"

  Configuration file is called Powerbattle.config.  It should be at S:

  Each line contains single setting.  Only first constant number
  string will be interpreted.  An example configuration:


  0                     Screenmode ID, only decimal numbers
  368                   Screen width
  282                   Screen height
  0                     InfoPanel on left side ?
  -1                    PanelButtons in use ?
  0                     Automatic Combat Report ?
  -1                    Sound Effects ?
  -1                    Automatic MoveTo ?
  4                     Unit move slide speed, 1 - 4
  4                     Scroll step on keys, n * 4


  Settings marked with ? should be set either True or False:

  -1    True
   0    False

  Only decimal number values are accepted

  If Configuration file is not found, the game will use built-in
  defaults.
@endnode



