@node star "Creating new battle"

  Recommended values for BIG (alfa) map & 4 players:

    60 coastal cities
    60 mainland cities
    15 starting cities
    50 technology-level

  - First four turns are 'protected'.  This means that no violence is
    allowed.  You may encounter enemy but you or he/she may not attack.
  - During protection turns, players get multiple 'turns' at time.

  In the beginning, produce T.Boat units in coastal cities & Mech Inf
  units in mainland cities.  Search for new cities -spread as fast as
  you can.  Next produce Settlers & make a road-net.  It is a good
  idea to produce Destroyers & Transports as soon as possible.
  Engineers can build bridges, this'll take 2 turns.
@endnode



@node move "Moving"

  In order to move:
  - Target hex must be of suitable Movement Type
  - Unit must have enough Movement Points
  - Fuel is needed in case of some units
  - There must be room for unit.  In single hex there may only be one
    of each Battle Type (One air unit, one ground etc.)
  - In cities there is room for 12 units, no matter what Battle
    Type they are.

  @{"Terrain Damage Threat System" link thre}
@endnode



@node thre "Terrain Damage Threat System"

  DamageThreat of terrain hex represents 'risk' that unit takes when
  moving in that hex.  Greater value means more risky hex, damage is
  more likely.

  Units' ThreatDefence tells how bad terrain it can handle.  Greater
  value means it can hadle worse terrains without taking damage.

  If DamageThreat is less than ThreatDefence, unit can't get damaged
  by moving.

  Otherwise, if DamageThreat is greater, increasing damage is likely.
  If ThreatDefence is only little lesser, usually a few hexes can be
  moved without serious damage.  But greater difference or distance
  will sooner or later prove fatal.
@endnode



@node comb "Closecombat & Ranged Attacks"

  Closecombat will begin, when you attemp to move to hex already
  occupied by enemy.  Ranged Attacks (Artillery for example) will be
  ordered by clicking RBM on target.

  In closecombat, first all attacker's hex's units in turn try to
  damage all units in defender's hex.  Then defender's hex will do the
  same thing.  And so on until either one hex is totally dead or both
  hexes have attacked 10 times.

  In ranged attacks, only the attacking unit will make a single
  damaging attemp to all units in defender's hex.  Some units have
  limited ammo storage.

  @{" EXAPLE           " link cmbe}
  @{" Combat Modifiers " link modi}
@endnode

@node modi "Combat Modifiers"

  A few modifiers can affect combat process:

  - Veteran Bonus.  'Green' units have modifier 1.0 (displayed 10).
    Experienced units may have up to 1.5 (displayed 15).
    Experience is gained in victorious combat against equal or greater
    unit (HitPoints).

  - Terrain Defence Bonus.  Forest for example can give significant
    cover to units.  Normal value 1.0 (displayed 10).

  - City Attack Modifier.  Especially bombers have different effect on
    cities and other ground targets.  Therefor, normal ground combat
    skill values may be lesser, but these will be multiplied up to 3.0
    if target is City Hex.

  - Ranged Attack Modifier.  Artillery units are efficient when used
    from range.  Their 'plain' combat skill values may be not a lot,
    thus making them poor at closecombat.  But combat skills will be
    multiplied by this modifier when attack is 'ranged'.

  - Light Ground Unit Modifier.  This feature was introduced to make
    Antitank efficient against armoured units but weak against
    unarmoured units.  So if target is unarmoured, combat values will
    be multiplied by this modifier. It might be between 0.1 and 2.0.
@endnode

@node cmbe "EXAMPLE of single damaging attempt"

  Attacker: Panzer - GROUND unit
  Defender: Bomber - AIR    unit

  LET  Max_Attack  = Panzer's     AIR-Attack
  LET  Max_Defence = Bomber's  GROUND-Defence

  At this point, Max values are @{"modified" link modi} to Max_Mod values.

  Modified values are Max_Mod_ -values.  Next:

  LET  Attack  = 25-100%  of  Max_Mod_Attack
  LET  Defence = 25-100%  of  Max_Mod_Defence
  LET  Damage  = Attack - Defence

  IF Damage is positive, defender's HitPoints is decreased by damage.
@endnode



@node tran "Transporters & Carriers"

  Transporters & Carriers can be used to transport, repair & refuel
  units.  Only AT-Fighters & AT-Bombers can use Carrier.


  Loading Procedure:
    - Set 'LoadPrep' on unit to be loaded.
      (You may need to cancel Temp. sentry)
    - Give 'Load' command to carrier or transporter.

  Unloading Procedure:
    - Select unit to be unloaded from tarnporter's/carrier's Cargo List
      on InfoPanel.

  Cancelling the Unload Procedure:
    - Click RMB on transporter/carrier.


  Normal Infantry can be unloaded from AirTRans ONLY in citties. Other
  infantry units can be unloaded anywhere.

  AirTransport can load units only in cities.
@endnode



@node repa "Repair & Refuel"

  Units are automatically repaired & refuelled in cities &
  traneporters / carriers.

  Cities will repair themselves when set not to produce anything, 'no
  orders'.
@endnode



@node spec "Special Abilities"

  - Settler can build road.
  - Engineers can build bridges.  Takes 2 turns.
  - Most units can change terrain to Plain.
  - Some units can build Fortress (f key) that'll have a good defence
    bonus.
  - 'Level' command will change several unit definitions:
    - defence will be enchanced
    - visibility & visible from -ranges will decrease
    - movement points will decrease
    - Ranged Attack modifier will change (artillery etc. attacks)
    - Range will change

    Level -command represents Infantry unit's ability to hide &
    submarine unit's ablity to dive.
@endnode






